		<img src="icon_posticon.gif" border="0" hspace="3"><font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="1">Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;03/29/2002&nbsp;:&nbsp; 05:36:25</font>

		&nbsp;<a href="pop_profile.asp?mode=display&id=3948"><img src="icon_profile.gif" height=15 width=15 alt="Show Profile" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>
        
			&nbsp;<a href="JavaScript:openWindow('pop_mail.asp?id=3948')"><img src="icon_email.gif" height=15 width=15 alt="Email Poster" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        &nbsp;<a href="JavaScript:openWindow('pop_messengers.asp?mode=ICQ&ICQ=43751860&M_NAME=Alaaraaf')"><img src="http://online.mirabilis.com/scripts/online.dll?icq=43751860&img=5" height=15 width=15 alt="Send Alaaraaf an ICQ Message" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=ReplyQuote&REPLY_ID=15412&TOPIC_ID=2142&FORUM_ID=3&CAT_ID=1&Forum_Title=Necromancer+Game+Guides&Topic_Title=Scarlet+desert+solo%3F&M="><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height=15 width=15 alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2"> Hey.</P><P>I just started hunting in the desert yesterday.  (Also level fifty-one!)  I've been hunting the revenants for preference and anything else I can get my hands on, while waiting on revenants to spawn.</P><P>As an Iksar, the Bloodtribe and Tro Jeg started out dubious.  I've left them be, simply so I don't have to deal with as many wanderers.  <i>(And there are a <b>lot</b> of Bloodtribe hangin' about.)</i>  If you zone in from The Grey, there is a ruin with three revenants a little to the South.  There is another ruin on the Southern edge of the zone, about halfway across.  <i>(Five revenants spawn here.)</i></P><P>The wanderers you need to watch out for are Lightcrawlers, Sunflowers and Scarlet Cheetahs.  These are all dark blue, with the occaisional light blue at level fifty-one.  Sadly, none of them drop anything!  <i>(I got an item I'm guessing is for a Twilight armour piece off a mis-named Lightcrawler, but that's it so far.)</i></P><P>The revenants <b>are</b> undead and thus effected by our undead spells.  They're also <b>really</b> resistant to being rooted.  I was using Root for a while, until I remembered Hungry Earth and was having a real hard time making it stick.  Even Hungry Earth can take half a dozen attempts, before it'll stick sometimes!  Otherwise, they're a little resistant, but not too bad.  <i>(Darkness sticks maybe two out of three times.)</i>  They hit pretty hard.  Doubling for 110 HPs will chew up your pet pretty swiftly.  JBoots will outrun them, though.  All the revenants have a proc which is a fairly weak DoT.  The Reavers cast Invoke Fear and Scourge, also.</P><P>Root and DoT is a little tricky, because of the resistance.  If you do opt for this, Dooming Darkness, Splurt and Envenomed Bolt are sufficient for the kill.  <i>(That amounts to around 2,800 HPs, no?)</i>  Replacing the EBolt with a Bond of Death leaves them with a slither of life, so it doesn't leave much leeway.  </P><P>Dread of Night works like a charm, so Fear kiting is very possible.  There's not too many problems with getting adds, so it works very nicely.  <i>(You get 61 HPs of damage out of Hungry Earth at level fifty-one, which is a nice little bonus, if you're let your pet beat on him while you drop all your DoTs and then Rooting.)</i>  The only problem I have with DoN, is the shortage of spell gems.  <i>(You need to keep Invoke Fear memmed as well, against the offchance that you get an add.)</i></P><P>I haven't tried sticking Ignite Blood on them yet, simply because I had EBolt memmed and I guessed that in a desert zone they might be fairly Fire resistant.</P><P>Every so often, you'll get a mis-named revenant pop.  These are the ones that drop the stuff for the Twilight armour quests.  <i>(None of the bits I have collected so far are NO DROP, but they're all LORE.)</i>  These have all conned light blue to me, but have substantially higher resistances than the others.</P><P>I haven't been up to the plateau as yet, but I'm told that the revenants there are about five levels higher.  However, since it is fairly regularly camped, I just left it alone.</P><P>Anyhow... Hope this helps.</P><P>AlAaraaf.</P><P></P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
